<item>
            <title>[LU-6298] sanity-hsm should shutdown CDTs in parallel</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6298</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Shutting down a copytool (by writing shutdown to mdt.lustre-MDT0000.hsm_control and waiting for mdt.lustre-MDT0000.hsm_control to contain stopped) takes about 8 seconds. In sanity-hsm.sh&apos;s copytool_cleanup() this is done is series for each MDT. Since copytool_cleanup() is called 95 times (with MDSCOUNT=4) this means that we waste about 95 * 3 * 8 == 2280 seconds per test run when compared to parallel shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
